The Window now has a @{" Menu " link MEN} .
Ability to load and save settings (Open..., Save, Save as...).
Autoconfigurating colours (adjustable via 'contrast').
Preferences-Format changed (old files unusable!).

@{" Directory Tree " link VER} with all changed files.
@endnode



@node ZUK "WBStars Guide (english)"
@prev NEU
@next COP
@toc toc
@{fg shine}@{bg text} About WBStars @{fg text}@{bg shine}
@{" Motivation        " link MOT}
@{" Technical         " link TEC}
@{" History           " link GES}
@{" Present (changes) " link NEU}@{fg shine}@{bg text}
  Future            @{fg text}@{bg shine}
@{" Copyright         " link COP}
@{" Sourcecode        " link SOU}
@{" Author            " link AUT}

@{" Installation " link INST}

@{" Usage " link BED}@{fg text}@{bg back}

There is one known problem that will be solved as fast as possible (I´m seraching for this bug for over 2 month )-:
- closing the WB-window in mode 1 will stop the drawing and you will be unable to quit WBStars

I´m thinking about the following enhancements:
-automatically calculate the number of stars that uses a constant amount of free CPU-time
-calculation of stars done with integers ( dramatic speed increase :-)
-some more nice pics

This version of WBStars works quite nice, and because of this I want to start developing WBStars2.0, that, additionally to the mentioned features and the @{" TNG-GUI " link "WBSPrefs/main"}, will have the following:
- modules (Warp, ASwarm, Firework, etc..)
- recognizes backgroundpictures (useful with MWBPattern, or sim.)
- runs in different windows and screens (in every window another module; bye, bye CPU ;)
- ARexx port (how about a program, that hunts the mousepointer with aswarm :-)
- DeliTracker Genies (Monoscope in the WB-Window...)
- and many more (send your ideas to @{" me " link AUT} , please)
@endnode



