@node SOU "WBStars Guide (english)"
@prev COP
@next AUT
@toc toc
@{fg shine}@{bg text} About WBStars @{fg text}@{bg shine}
@{" Motivation        " link MOT}
@{" Technical         " link TEC}
@{" History           " link GES}
@{" Present (changes) " link NEU}
@{" Future            " link ZUK}
@{" Copyright         " link COP}@{fg shine}@{bg text}
  Sourcecode        @{fg text}@{bg shine}
@{" Author            " link AUT}

@{" Installation " link INST}

@{" Usage " link BED}@{fg text}@{bg back}

In this version the sourcecode is included (WBStars/source).

The GUI is done with GadToolsBox (.gui file also included).

The sourcecode is not copyrighted, as long as you do not use the name WBStars, and you do not make me responsible for your programs.

If anyone uses parts (or all) of my code, i would like to be mentioned and/or notified of this.

To compile the code you can use (with SAS/C 5.10b) the included makefile (you will need to do a assign to WBStars: ) . If you don´t want to use the makefile link with cback.o (or similar) to make it run as a background process, or you must start the programm with run (or DONOTWAIT,respectively).

I hope including the source will led to many improvement proposals.
@endnode



