@node VOR "WBStars Guide (english)"
@prev INST
@next INS
@toc toc
@{bg shine}@{" About WBStars " link WBS}

@{fg shine}@{bg text} Installation 
  Requirements   @{fg text}@{bg shine}
@{" Installation   " link INS}
@{" Directory Tree " link VER}

@{" Usage " link BED}@{bg back}

This program needs WB2.0 (V36) or higher, because it uses the commodities.library .

It may use a lot of CPU-time (I hope, this will change in the near @{" future " link ZUK} ). For WBStars881 you need in addition to the coprocessor at least a MC68020.

It is @{b}not@{ub} required to be a member of the United Federation of Trekkies ;).
@endnode



@node INS "WBStars Guide (english)"
@prev VOR
@next VER
@toc toc
@{bg shine}@{" About WBStars " link WBS}

@{fg shine}@{bg text} Installation @{fg text}@{bg shine}
@{" Requirements   " link VOR}@{fg shine}@{bg text}
  Installation   @{fg text}@{bg shine}
@{" Directory Tree " link VER}

@{" Usage " link BED}@{bg back}

To install WBStars, just drag the directory to any place you like (if WBStars1.2 is already installed, see @{" Directory Tree " link VER} for the files, that have changed).

If you want to start WBStars every time you boot, move the file "WBStarsUp.info" to "SYS:WBStartup" and change the default tool of the icon (you can also start WBStars from startup-sequence; without "run", because it is automatically started in the background ).

IMPORTANT:
To see the stars you may have to set the correct backgroundpen with the @{" GUI " link GUI}!
@endnode



